              <br/>I was born in a Muslim home but was caught up in an  encounter while in secondary school.  Couldnt attend any fellowship then outside school hours because either my Dad or Mom would be  waiting to pick me home immediately after school hours.
              <br/>During my ALevel classes at ISI,  Late Mrs Aransiola, cant remember what she taught then usually encourage us to  make sure we  get hooked to a fellowship once we gain admission. On getting to UI,  my Dad informed the Muslim society that his daughter was on campus,  so they pursued me and I kept running.
              <br/>I was moving from one church and fellowship to the other on campus asking for the leading of the Holy Spirit to know where he want me to be. I even attend IVCU once I think but was not fulfilled. Some how I came to chapel area one Sunday and I saw this small group.
              <br/>I joined the fellowship,  was blessed and knew this is the place for me.  That fellowship was SCM.  I used to be very shy,  so shy that I cant look at people straight in the eyes,  so that kept me  glued to the seat and didnt serve in the fellowship. Also was being careful of the Muslim brethren,  because they really pursued me to  get me back.
